Package gui

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bang
    BANG is a scrambled acronym which stands for
    Alpha, Beta, Gamma analysis (both theoretical and experimental)
    and Nuclide data, public exposures, dosimetry and shielding (X-ray included).
    It is a modular application also known as RadiationHelper!
    BangAboutFrame
    The About window displays some information about the application.
    KClCalculator
    Class designed to compute the activity of 40K contained in a KCl sample (potassium chloride).
    LongTimeStability
    Class for testing the Long time stability for alpha, beta and gamma detectors.
    Long time stability is all about measuring a standard test source (counts per seconds for alpha and beta devices or Net area in counts per seconds for the peak of interest in case of gamma detector) at various time intervals (e.g.
    SelfAbsorptionFrame
    Class designed to study the self absorbtion effect for detectors.
